27/03/2005
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Macedonia signed an agreement on Friday (25 March) dealing with exchanges of classified information with the EU. 
The head of the Macedonian directorate for security and protection of classified information, Stojan Slavevski, said the move is part of Macedonia's efforts to move closer to EU accession as well as an important step towards liberalisation of the EU visa regime for Macedonian citizens. 
(A1 TV - 25/03/05)
